Key Match Events: Jared McCain put up 34 points and 10 assists in his first career start.
Donovan Mitchell scored 11 of his 23 points in the last three minutes, including three triples.
The Cavaliers improved to 13-0, becoming the sixth team in NBA history to start a season with such a record.
Post-Match Reflections: Jared McCain emphasized the importance of visualization in his performance.
Coach Nick Nurse praised McCain's ability to read the defense and share the ball.
Caleb Martin expressed optimism about the team's progress despite the loss.
